# Connect firebase with flutter

Steps
if system is new for this
1. Download node js form internet with latest version
2. install the node js
3. install firebase {command: npm install -g firebase-tools}
4. login firebase with firebase account credentail {command: firebase login}
5. install flutter_cli  {command: dart pub global activate flutterfire_cli}
6. connect firebase project id with {flutterfire configure --project=projectId}
7. select your platform for project with arrow and space buttons
8. if need => pass the project id for android
9. press enter and it will download the require files
10. add 'firebase_core' package
Note: Internet should be connected with system.

